{"type":null,"faqId":47451,"title":"Why doesn't the screen turn on when I double touch the screen?","answer":"<p style=\"LINE-HEIGHT: 12pt; MARGIN: 8pt 0in 8pt 85.05pt; LAYOUT-GRID-MODE: char; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman','serif'; FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt; punctuation-trim: leading\">Make sure the <b>Double touch</b> switch is turned on in <b>Settings</b> &gt; <b>Motion control</b> &gt; <b>Double touch</b>. If it is turned on, make sure you double touch correctly according. Note the following:</p>\n<p style=\"LINE-HEIGHT: 12pt; TEXT-INDENT: -21.25pt; MARGIN: 4pt 0in 4pt 106.3pt; LAYOUT-GRID-MODE: char; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman','serif'; FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt; tab-stops: list 106.3pt\"><span style=\"POSITION: relative; FONT-FAMILY: Wingdings; FONT-SIZE: 8pt; TOP: -1pt\"><span>l<span style=\"FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>The area within 1 cm from the edge of the screen does not recognize touches.</p>\n<p style=\"LINE-HEIGHT: 12pt; TEXT-INDENT: -21.25pt; MARGIN: 4pt 0in 4pt 106.3pt; LAYOUT-GRID-MODE: char; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman','serif'; FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt; tab-stops: list 106.3pt\"><span style=\"POSITION: relative; FONT-FAMILY: Wingdings; FONT-SIZE: 8pt; TOP: -1pt\"><span>l<span style=\"FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>The interval between touches must not exceed 500 ms.</p>\n<p style=\"LINE-HEIGHT: 12pt; TEXT-INDENT: -21.25pt; MARGIN: 4pt 0in 4pt 106.3pt; LAYOUT-GRID-MODE: char; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman','serif'; FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt; tab-stops: list 106.3pt\"><span style=\"POSITION: relative; FONT-FAMILY: Wingdings; FONT-SIZE: 8pt; TOP: -1pt\"><span>l<span style=\"FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>The distance between touches must not exceed 5 mm.</p>\n<p style=\"LINE-HEIGHT: 12pt; TEXT-INDENT: -21.25pt; MARGIN: 4pt 0in 4pt 106.3pt; LAYOUT-GRID-MODE: char; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman','serif'; FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt; tab-stops: list 106.3pt\"><span style=\"POSITION: relative; FONT-FAMILY: Wingdings; FONT-SIZE: 8pt; TOP: -1pt\"><span>l<span style=\"FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>Don't try to turn on the screen in this way immediately after locking the screen. The screen only recognizes your touches 800 ms after turning off.</p>\n<p style=\"LINE-HEIGHT: 12pt; TEXT-INDENT: -21.25pt; MARGIN: 4pt 0in 4pt 106.3pt; LAYOUT-GRID-MODE: char; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman','serif'; FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt; tab-stops: list 106.3pt\"><span style=\"POSITION: relative; FONT-FAMILY: Wingdings; FONT-SIZE: 8pt; TOP: -1pt\"><span>l<span style=\"FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>When double touching, make sure not to block the light sensor. If you block or touch near the light sensor, your touches will not be recognized. </p>","faqTypeId":null,"faqType":null,"useful":4,"unUseful":0,"languageId":242,"languageName":"id","faqCode":"2959","faqTypeCode":null,"isTop":"0","moduleCode":"faq","productId":null,"productCode":null,"postDate":1445223837000,"seriesProductName":"RIO-L01","visitedTimes":258,"isUsefulFlag":null,"score":0,"times":0,"imageList":null,"displayType":"text","justView":"0","fileName":null,"filePath":null,"imagePath":null,"imageName":null,"productIdList":null,"curPage":null,"pageSize":null,"siteCode":null,"statusFlag":"Publish","returnCode":0,"totalRows":null,"keywords":null,"avgScore":0.0,"createDate":null,"totalPages":null}